{"lemma":"دِمامٌ","slug":"دِمامٌ","root":"د.م.م","root_slug":"د-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/د-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13033","n13036"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"ugly, hideous"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb دَمَّ (damma, “to become ugly”)."},"ipa":["/da.miːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13033","headword_ar":"دِمَامٌ","root":"dm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~N","text_ar":"دَمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one smears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"does over,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the face"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) said by some to be the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red pigment with which women redden their faces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and particularly, [i. e. both these words,] (K,) or the former, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a medicinal liniment with which one smears the forehead of a child"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the exterior of his eyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or the former word,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a medicament with which the forehead of a child is smeared, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuDaD","text_ar":"حُضَض"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuDuD","text_ar":"حُضُض"},{"kind":"text","text":": and as some say, [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pigment called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naw^uwr","text_ar":"نَوُور"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collyrium,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liniment, that is applied to the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any medicament with which the exterior of the eye is smeared;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as aloes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saffron:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naw^uwrN","text_ar":"نَوُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is applied to the gums. (T.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buS~irato","text_ar":"بُصِّرَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidimaAmK","text_ar":"بِدِمَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of the feathers of an arrow, means"},{"kind":"page_break","n":911},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They were stuck fast with glue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they were besmeared with blood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bSr","text_ar":"بصر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  Also, [i. e. both words,] (K,) or the former word, (T,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds in which is no water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) as being likened to the liniment so called. (TA)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n13036","headword_ar":"دَمَّامٌ","root":"dm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who repairs cooking-pots by cementing them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Golius from Meyd. See 1.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AF%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85/","headword_ar":"دمامي","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_48","lexicon_en":"Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)","lexicon_ar":"موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=111766#451825","body_html":"دمامي<br>عن العبرية بمعنى هدأ وصمت ووقف والياء للنسب. يستخدم للذكور."}]}}